id: pm-g5sx
title: "Tracker merge semantics: field-aware merge guidance, history-chain-safe JSONL merging, and post-merge reconciliation for multi-branch agent workflows"
description: "Define and tool what 'mergeable' means for .agents/pm data when branches/worktrees mutate the same items: per-artifact merge semantics (.toon items, hash-chained history JSONL, runtime/index), .gitattributes or merge-driver guidance, and a post-merge validate/doctor advisory that detects conflict markers, diverged history chains, and duplicate IDs with remediation hints."
type: Feature
status: open
priority: 3
tags[6]: "area:sdk",git,long-term,multi-agent,scale,storage
created_at: "2026-07-06T22:56:01.193Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-06T22:56:01.193Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 480
acceptance_criteria: Documented merge semantics for every tracker artifact class; post-merge detection surfaced via validate or health with remediation hints wiring into history-repair; worktree/branch agent workflow documented in AGENT_GUIDE; any merge tooling ships SDK-first with the CLI as a shim
parent: pm-o2kc
risk: medium
confidence: medium
body: "## Context\nGit-native storage is a hard constraint (ADR pm-i7i4: the filesystem is the database; ADR pm-bl8x decision driver: everything must remain \"diffable, mergeable, and recoverable from the working tree alone\"). But pm has never defined what \"mergeable\" actually means when two branches mutate the same item: worktree agents branch from main today, and at thousands of concurrent agents, branch-and-merge becomes a primary workflow, not an edge case.\n\n## Problem\n- Two branches editing the same `.toon` item file produce raw git conflicts with no field-aware resolution guidance (last-writer-wins on a whole file loses the other branch's fields).\n- History JSONL streams are hash-chained (appendLineAtomic anchoring): a naive union merge of two diverged `history/<id>.jsonl` files breaks chain integrity; `pm history-repair` (shipped in pm-85hm) can re-anchor drift but is not merge-aware and must be invoked manually per item.\n- There is no post-merge verification story: `pm validate` / `pm health` do not flag \"this workspace was just merged and N history chains diverged / M items have conflict markers\".\n\n## Deliverables (scope for grooming)\n1. Documented merge semantics per artifact class: item `.toon` (field-level three-way guidance or documented ours/theirs policy), history `.jsonl` (union + mandatory re-anchor), locks/runtime (ignore), search index (rebuild).\n2. `.gitattributes` recommendations and, if justified, a custom git merge driver shipped as a pm package (check existing unbraind packages first — none cover this as of 2026-07-07 audit #16).\n3. Post-merge reconciliation entrypoint: e.g. `pm validate --post-merge` advisory or doctor check that detects conflict markers, diverged chains, and duplicate IDs from parallel branch creation (relates to pm-khdq ID TOCTOU), with remediation hints wiring into history-repair.\n4. Docs: worktree/branch agent workflow guidance (AGENT_GUIDE) covering when to branch tracker data vs. mutate main.\n\n## Relationships\n- pm-is1a (multi-workspace federation) is the superset problem; single-workspace multi-branch merge is the prerequisite and should land first.\n- SDK-first (pm-usfg): reconciliation logic lands as an SDK primitive; CLI is a shim.\n- Horizon: long (with pm-9rxu scale-out); design/ADR input can start earlier.\n\n## Duplicate check (2026-07-07 audit #16)\nSearched \"merge conflict branch tracker\", \"merge driver git worktree branches\", \"post-merge reconcile history chain\" — only history-repair (pm-85hm, shipped, drift-only) and consolidation item pm-tqel matched; no existing item covers merge semantics or post-merge reconciliation."
